Statements made as to sentencing.  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 YEARS, with credit for 54 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 MONTHS.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 30 MONTHS with the following conditions:  
1) Serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction; may earn GOOD TIME; release for the Day Reporting Center for treatment and other programming; 
2) Referred to the Mental Health Unit for assessment/treatment deemed appropriate; 
3) Take all prescribed meds by treating physician; 
4) Obtain GED/HSED; 
5) Perform 50 hours of community service; 
6) Cooperate with agent - no new violations of the law which rises to the level of probable cause;
7) Pay restitution in the amount of $2314.00 to Debra F.;
8) Provide a DNA sample;
9) Pay all remaining costs, assessments and surcharges;
10) No contact with John D. or Debra F.

Court ordered the DNA surcharge waived due to the defendant's limited income and the restitution and costs that must be paid.
If the defendant is revoked, Court ordered that the restitution, costs and surcharges be paid out of up to 25% of prison accounts and to be collected and distributed by the Department of Corrections; balance to be paid during extended supervision; if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.  Court ordered the restitution be paid first.
